window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>An Ufthak Blackhawk Audiobook</p> <p>Ufthak Blackhawk reckons he’s in for it. Da Meklord has summoned him, and the Gargantsmasha just knows his boss wants to kick his teef in and be done with it.</p> <p>LISTEN TO IT BECAUSE</p> <p>Ufthak Blackhawk faces the Drukhari in the teeming flesh pits of their dark city of Commorragh as he finds himself challenged to gladiatorial combat against the masters of pain.</p> <p>THE STORY</p> <p>Out of options, Ufthak leads his Waaagh! through the mysterious webway, to a place where kunnin’, sneakin’, and thinkin’ are the name of the game. A place with little truck for muscle and brawn – Commorragh, the Dark City.</p> <p>Here, where kabals and haemonculus covens pump psychic viscera into the warp, Ufthak is thrown into gladiatorial combat and soon finds himself up against an archon who will stop at nothing to prove she deserves to rule the Dark City – even if it means bringing Commorragh down around her.</p> <p>But the Drukhari are about to discover that while orks may be simple, very little about them is ever straightforward.</p>"; 
